---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Bert Liu — Taiwan Manufacturing Field Notes</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Field notes from Taiwan’s factory floor for North American hardware teams navigating production, supplier coordination, and quality control."
    />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://bertliu.com/" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="any" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Bert Liu" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Bert Liu — Taiwan Manufacturing Field Notes" />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="Field notes from Taiwan’s factory floor for North American hardware teams navigating production, supplier coordination, and quality control."
    />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://bertliu.com/" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://bertliu.com/og-image.jpg" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Bert Liu — Taiwan Manufacturing Field Notes" />
    <meta
      name="twitter:description"
      content="Field notes from Taiwan’s factory floor for North American hardware teams navigating production, supplier coordination, and quality control."
    />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://bertliu.com/og-image.jpg" />
    <style>
      :root {
        --bg: #f7f4ed;
        --text: #1f1f1b;
        --muted: #4e4a42;
        --line: #d8d2c5;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html {
        overflow-y: scroll;
        scrollbar-gutter: stable;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
        color: var(--text);
        background: var(--bg);
        line-height: 1.65;
      }

      h1,
      h2,
      h3,
      nav,
      .intro-links,
      .article-date,
      .carousel-status {
        font-family:
          ui-sans-serif,
          system-ui,
          -apple-system,
          BlinkMacSystemFont,
          "Segoe UI",
          sans-serif;
      }

      .page {
        width: min(1100px, 100%);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 40px 24px 80px;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 220px minmax(0, 1fr);
        column-gap: 56px;
      }

      nav {
        position: sticky;
        top: 48px;
        align-self: start;
        width: 180px;
      }

      nav ul {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      nav a {
        color: var(--muted);
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
        padding-bottom: 2px;
      }

      nav a:hover,
      nav a:focus-visible {
        color: var(--text);
        border-bottom-color: var(--line);
      }

      nav a[aria-current="page"] {
        color: var(--text);
        font-weight: 600;
        border-bottom-color: var(--line);
      }

      main {
        grid-column: 2;
        max-width: 750px;
      }

      .intro {
        padding: 0 0 28px;
      }

      .intro-head {
        display: flex;
        align-items: baseline;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 16px;
        margin: 0 0 4px;
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 5vw, 2.4rem);
        font-weight: 500;
        letter-spacing: 0.01em;
        line-height: 1.05em;
      }

      .intro-links {
        display: flex;
        gap: 12px;
        align-items: center;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
      }

      .intro-links a {
        color: var(--muted);
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
        padding-bottom: 1px;
      }

      .intro-links a:hover,
      .intro-links a:focus-visible {
        color: var(--text);
        border-bottom-color: var(--line);
      }



      section {
        padding: 36px 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      }

      h2 {
        margin: 0 0 12px;
        font-size: 1.45rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }

      p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .intro p {
  margin: 0;
  max-width: 70ch;
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 1.2rem;
}

      .intro .intro-positioning {
        margin-top: 10px;
        max-width: 70ch;
        font-size: 1rem;
      }

      .feature-article {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 320px) minmax(0, 1fr);
        gap: 24px;
        align-items: start;
      }

      .article-header {
        margin: 0 0 16px;
      }

      .article-title {
        margin: 0 0 6px;
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.6vw, 1.8rem);
        font-weight: 550;
        line-height: 1.25;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }

      .article-date {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.88rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.01em;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      .article-images {
        margin: 0;
        display: grid;
        gap: 10px;
        min-width: 0;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .article-images img {
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
      }

      .article-images [hidden] {
        display: none;
      }

      .video-card {
        position: relative;
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        aspect-ratio: 3 / 2;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        background: #000;
        cursor: pointer;
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .video-card img {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
        border: none;
        display: block;
      }

      .video-card__play {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        width: 54px;
        height: 54px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: rgba(20, 20, 18, 0.6);
        display: grid;
        place-items: center;
        transition: background 0.15s ease;
      }

      .video-card:hover .video-card__play,
      .video-card:focus-visible .video-card__play {
        background: rgba(20, 20, 18, 0.82);
      }

      .video-card__play svg {
        width: 22px;
        height: 22px;
        margin-left: 2px;
        fill: #fff;
      }

      .video-overlay {
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        z-index: 1000;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        padding: 24px;
        background: rgba(15, 15, 12, 0.92);
      }

      .video-overlay[hidden] {
        display: none;
      }

      .video-overlay__player {
        max-width: min(1100px, 100%);
        max-height: 88vh;
        background: #000;
      }

      .video-overlay__image {
        display: block;
        max-width: min(1100px, 100%);
        max-height: 88vh;
        width: auto;
        height: auto;
        object-fit: contain;
        background: #000;
      }

      .video-overlay [hidden] {
        display: none;
      }

      [data-carousel-image] {
        cursor: zoom-in;
      }

      .video-overlay__close {
        position: absolute;
        top: 14px;
        right: 18px;
        width: 40px;
        height: 40px;
        font-size: 1.9rem;
        line-height: 1;
        color: #fff;
        background: none;
        border: none;
        cursor: pointer;
      }

      .carousel-controls {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        min-width: 0;
      }

      .carousel-thumb {
        position: relative;
        width: 56px;
        height: 56px;
        padding: 0;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        background: transparent;
        cursor: pointer;
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .carousel-thumb-play {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
        width: 22px;
        height: 22px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: rgba(20, 20, 18, 0.7);
        display: grid;
        place-items: center;
      }

      .carousel-thumb-play svg {
        width: 10px;
        height: 10px;
        margin-left: 1px;
        fill: #fff;
      }

      .carousel-thumb img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
        display: block;
      }

      .carousel-thumb.active {
        border-color: var(--text);
      }

      .carousel-status {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 0.92rem;
      }

      .article-body p + p {
        margin-top: 14px;
      }

      .article-list {
        margin: 10px 0 14px 20px;
        padding: 0;
        color: var(--muted);
      }

      .article-list li + li {
        margin-top: 3px;
      }

      .text-article {
        margin-top: 42px;
        padding-top: 34px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      }

      .worklog-post + .worklog-post {
        margin-top: 56px;
        padding-top: 42px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      }

      @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .page {
          display: block;
          padding: 20px 20px 56px;
        }

        nav {
          position: static;
          width: auto;
          margin-bottom: 24px;
          border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
          padding-bottom: 12px;
        }

        nav ul {
          flex-direction: row;
          flex-wrap: wrap;
          gap: 10px 18px;
        }

        .intro {
          padding: 0 0 24px;
        }

        .intro-head {
          align-items: flex-end;
          flex-wrap: wrap;
          margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        section {
          padding: 28px 0;
        }

        .feature-article {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .article-images {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
          gap: 12px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <nav aria-label="Main navigation">
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/" aria-current="page">Field Notes</a></li>
          <li><a href="/manufacturing-stack">Manufacturing Stack</a></li>
          <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>

      <main>
        <header class="intro">
          <div class="intro-head">
            <h1>Bert Liu</h1>
            <div class="intro-links" aria-label="Social links">
              <a
                href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bertmfg/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                aria-label="LinkedIn">in</a
              >
              <a
                href="https://www.instagram.com/bertbuilds/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                aria-label="Instagram">ig</a
              >
              <a href="mailto:bert@bertliu.com" aria-label="Email">✉</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>
            Manufacturing in Taiwan. Notes on factories, systems, and supply chains.
          </p>
        </header>

        <section id="worklog">
          <article class="worklog-post">
            <div class="article-header">
              <h3 class="article-title">
                NCT Field Notes: Quality Control at the Source
              </h3>
              <p class="article-date">
                <strong>June 6, 2026</strong> · Taiwan · Sheet Metal / NCT / Quality Control / Sourcing
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-article">
              <div class="article-images" data-carousel>
                <img
                  data-carousel-image
                  src={nctSheetFab1.src}
                  alt="Bert working hands-on beside an NCT turret punch machine on a sheet metal factory floor."
                  loading="lazy"
                />

                <div
                  class="carousel-controls"
                  aria-label="Article image carousel controls"
                >
                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb active"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="0"
                    aria-label="Show NCT turret punch setup photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={nctSheetFab1.src}
                      alt="NCT turret punch setup photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="1"
                    aria-label="Show DFM review photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={nctSheetFab2.src}
                      alt="DFM review photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="2"
                    aria-label="Show NCT machine photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={nctSheetFab3.src}
                      alt="NCT machine photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="3"
                    aria-label="Show setup sheet and punched panel photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={nctSheetFab4.src}
                      alt="Setup sheet and punched panel photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="4"
                    aria-label="Show welding hardware onto formed sheet metal panel photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={nctSheetFab5.src}
                      alt="Welding hardware onto formed sheet metal panel photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="5"
                    aria-label="Show first article inspection photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={nctSheetFab6.src}
                      alt="First article inspection photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="6"
                    aria-label="Show finished sheet metal panel photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={nctSheetFab7.src}
                      alt="Finished sheet metal panel photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <span class="carousel-status" data-carousel-status>1 / 7</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="article-body">
                <p>
                  A capability deck tells you a factory can make your part. It does not tell you they made yours right.
                </p>

                <p>
                  When you are scaling a high-value order from the other side of the world, the riskiest stretch usually is not choosing the supplier. It is the gap between the PO and the delivery — when the part is actually being built, decisions are being made, and no one from the customer’s side is in the room.
                </p>

                <p>
                  That is the part I care about most, so I spend time on the floor.
                </p>

                <p>
                  It starts before any machine runs: the sheet itself. Right gauge, right finish, right material — no quiet substitution that nobody flags until it shows up as a field failure.
                </p>

                <p>
                  Then the part lives on a screen for a while. Sitting with the engineer over the DFM, you catch the spec problems while they are still pixels — the feature that fights the tooling, the tolerance that will not hold, the drawing decision that turns into production pain later.
                </p>

                <p>
                  On the floor, the NCT turret does the punching, but only after the right tools are loaded and checked against the setup sheet. Wrong tool, wrong sequence, wrong assumption, and you have lost a shift — which means you have lost lead time the customer was counting on to the day.
                </p>

                <p>
                  Then bending. Then welding — hardware onto the formed panel, where heat and fixturing decide whether it stays flat or pulls out of tolerance.
                </p>

                <p>
                  Then the first article, measured against the drawing before the rest are allowed to follow.
                </p>

                <p>
                  But the real question is whether the thousandth part is as good as the first — and whether someone catches the drift before it ships.
                </p>

                <p>
                  When the stakes are high and the customer is an ocean away, the value is not a quality report after the fact. It is someone in the room who knows what correct looks like at each step, and catches the problem while there is still time to fix it.
                </p>

                <p>
                  I can do that because I have been hands-on with the process and learned where the details and bottlenecks really show up. You cannot understand that only by watching from a distance.
                </p>

                <p>
                  That is the work.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
                    <article class="worklog-post">
            <div class="article-header">
              <h3 class="article-title">
                Phone Cooling Is a Packaging Problem
              </h3>
              <p class="article-date">
                <strong>June 5, 2026</strong> · Taipei, Taiwan · R&D / Thermal Management / Injection Molding / Mechanical Integration
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-article">
              <div class="article-images" data-carousel>
                <img
                  data-carousel-image
                  src={deltaPhoneCooling1.src}
                  alt="Bert with Delta R&D at Computex discussing AI smartphone micro cooling fans and thermal device solutions."
                  loading="lazy"
                />

                <div
                  class="carousel-controls"
                  aria-label="Article image carousel controls"
                >
                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb active"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="0"
                    aria-label="Show Delta phone cooling Computex photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={deltaPhoneCooling1.src}
                      alt="Delta phone cooling Computex photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="1"
                    aria-label="Show phone internal packaging photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={deltaPhoneCooling2.src}
                      alt="Phone internal packaging photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="2"
                    aria-label="Show phone micro fan close-up photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={deltaPhoneCooling3.src}
                      alt="Phone micro fan close-up photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="3"
                    aria-label="Show hidden airflow path photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={deltaPhoneCooling4.src}
                      alt="Hidden airflow path photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <span class="carousel-status" data-carousel-status>1 / 4</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="article-body">
                <p>
                  One thing I enjoy about Computex is getting to ask dumb questions.
                </p>

                <p>
                  Looking at this Delta micro fan, my first thought was: if AI servers are moving toward liquid cooling, why aren’t phones doing the same?
                </p>

                <p>
                  The R&amp;D engineer’s answer was surprisingly simple.
                </p>

                <p>
                  Phones don’t have the space.
                </p>

                <p>
                  This fan sits near the camera area because that’s one of the few places with usable volume left once cameras, batteries, processors, antennas, and everything else are fighting for space.
                </p>

                <p>
                  But the more interesting detail was what happens after the fan moves air.
                </p>

                <p>
                  The airflow path is hidden inside the housing.
                </p>

                <p>
                  Small outlet pockets. Woven mesh inserts. Molded plastic features. Bonded or heat-staked edges. Dust control. Vibration control.
                </p>

                <p>
                  At that scale, cooling is not just a thermal problem.
                </p>

                <p>
                  It is a packaging and manufacturing problem.
                </p>

                <p>
                  The fan blades are incredibly thin, pushing the limits of injection molding and precision manufacturing while still needing to survive years of vibration, dust exposure, drops, and daily use.
                </p>

                <p>
                  One pattern I noticed throughout Computex: the most interesting engineering is not always the newest technology.
                </p>

                <p>
                  Sometimes it is pushing an existing technology right to its limit inside a space where every millimeter is already taken.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
          <article class="worklog-post">
            <div class="article-header">
              <h3 class="article-title">
                Computex Field Notes: AI Cooling Is a Manufacturing Capability Problem
              </h3>
              <p class="article-date">
                <strong>June 4, 2026</strong> · Taipei, Taiwan · Computex / Manufacturing / Thermal Management / Supplier Capability / Quality / AI Infrastructure
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-article">
              <div class="article-images" data-carousel>
                <img
                  data-carousel-image
                  src={computexCoolingEcosystem1.src}
                  alt="Bert with a VAV Cooling R&D engineer at Computex, standing in front of stainless cooling components and manifolds."
                  loading="lazy"
                />

                <div
                  class="carousel-controls"
                  aria-label="Article image carousel controls"
                >
                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb active"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="0"
                    aria-label="Show VAV Cooling R&D booth photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={computexCoolingEcosystem1.src}
                      alt="VAV Cooling R&D booth photo thumbnail"
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
                    class="carousel-thumb"
                    type="button"
                    data-carousel-thumb
                    data-index="1"
                    aria-label="Show Delta pump design concept photo"
                  >
                    <img
                      src={computexCoolingEcosystem2.src}
                      alt="Exploded view of Delta pump design concept for AI cooling infrastructure."
                      loading="lazy"
                    />
                  </button>

                  <button
